The paper proposes a new framework for multi-objective deep reinforcement learning, which involves the use of deep Q-networks. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The framework also involves the use of reinforcement learning in complex environments, which could be categorized under robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of deep neural networks in the proposed framework could also be categorized under neural networks (cs.NE).
